import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  

export default class MDXContent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props)
    this.layout = null
  }
  render() {
    const { components, ...props } = this.props

    return <MDXTag
             name="wrapper"
             
             components={components}><MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"web-checklist"}}>{`Web Checklist`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`(to finish)`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"things-to-write-about"}}>{`Things to write about`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="ol" components={components}>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ol">{`Lazyloading`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ol">{`Lighthouse`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ol">{`Image Compression`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ol">{`Accessibility`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ol">{`SEO`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ol">{`Cache headers`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"cache-headers"}}>{`Cache Headers`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="ol" components={components}>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ol">{`S3 bucket - add there`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ol">{`CloudFront - add there`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"s3-bucket"}}>{`S3 Bucket`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}><MDXTag name="inlineCode" components={components} parentName="p">{`aws s3 sync build s3://git-good-sites/ --recursive --cache-control max-age=31536000`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"cloudfront"}}>{`CloudFront`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Head onto the website and add it there.`}</MDXTag>
           </MDXTag>
  }
}
